  "diff": "Expected AUC>0.70 for composite failure — got 0.643 (BELOW target). Zero-output AUC=0.730 (meets target separately). Expected <20% vs >40% failure rate at Re_crit=1.575 — got 25% vs 33.3% (WEAK, not clinically significant, n=12 laminar). Turbulent fail less: weakly confirmed but trivial separation (8pp). Key surprise: era dominates — Mature (S360+) has 0% failure rate (n=9). Re_structural distribution spans 4 orders of magnitude (0.99 to 46817) because near-zero overhead produces division explosion. The Reynolds analog failure-detection power (AUC=0.643) is WEAKER than productivity-prediction power (S376 AUC=0.870). For failure, protocol maturity (era) > session structure (Re). Re_structural is a productivity correlate, not a failure predictor.",
